            "body": "options doc says:\r\n\r\n\r\n> custom: comma-separated list of exactly 8 characters in clockwise order starting from topleft.\r\n\r\nsuggested update:\r\n\r\n```\r\n  - custom: comma-separated list of exactly 8 entries in clockwise order\r\n    starting from topleft. Each entry may be a single char, a single\r\n    space (filled with bg), or empty (no border on that side).\r\n    Example: >lua\r\n         vim.o.winborder='+,-,+,|,+,-,+,|'\r\n         vim.o.winborder=',, , ,, , ,'  -- left/right padding only\r\n```",
            "created_at": "2026-06-04T11:15:39Z",
